"title": "5038: mind, the human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5038: mind, the human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>On account of its inner orientation the fallen human mind is in conflict with the mind of God. It is nevertheless capable of knowing God, and of being changed and renewed by him.</p>\n<h2>The human mind is the seat of reason and decision-making</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:1-Job12:3\">JOB 12:1–12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:2\">1CH 17:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:11\">2CH 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:7\">NEH 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:14\">PSA 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:3\">PSA 49:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:28\">PRO 15:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:21\">PRO 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:3\">ECC 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:16\">ECC 8:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:16\">DAN 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:12\">DAN 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:1\">DAN 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:10\">ROM 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:5\">ROM 14:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:14-1Cor14:15\">1CO 14:14–14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:13\">1PE 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:9\">REV 17:9</a></p>\n<h2>The fallen human mind</h2>\n<h3>The human mind is fatally flawed by sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9\">JER 17:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5\">GEN 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:21\">GEN 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:14\">2CH 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:9\">PSA 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:6\">PSA 64:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:7\">PSA 73:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:6\">ISA 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:8\">ROM 8:5–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:17-Eph4:18\">EPH 4:17–4:18</a></p>\n<h3>Even the fallen mind can know something of God through creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:19-Rom1:20\">ROM 1:19–1:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The fallen mind tends to confuse the Creator with his creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:16-Isa44:18\">ISA 44:16–44:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:21-Rom1:25\">ROM 1:21–1:25</a></p>\n<h2>Consequences of the human mind's sinfulness</h2>\n<h3>Sinful attitudes lead to sinful words and actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:19\">MAT 15:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:21-Mark7:22\">MRK 7:21–7:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:28-Rom1:32\">ROM 1:28–1:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:17-Eph4:19\">EPH 4:17–4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:18\">COL 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:8\">2TI 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Sinfulness leads to death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21\">COL 1:21</a></p>\n<h3>Doubt and instability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:6-Jas1:8\">JAS 1:6–1:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God can change the attitudes of the sinful human mind</h2>\n<h3>The mind can be convicted of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3\">PSA 51:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:44\">1KI 2:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:8-John16:11\">JHN 16:8–16:11</a></p>\n<h3>The mind can be changed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:9\">1TH 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:26\">2CH 32:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:6\">JOB 42:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:36\">PSA 119:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:17–26:18</a></p>\n<h3>It is God who enlightens the mind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:6\">2CO 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:4\">DEU 29:4</a> <em>God may withhold understanding</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:9\">1SA 10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:36\">JOB 38:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:4\">ISA 32:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:7\">JER 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:39\">JER 32:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:19\">EZK 11:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:31\">EZK 18:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26-Ezek36:27\">EZK 36:26–36:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:14\">2CO 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>It is God who renews the human mind</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3-Titus3:7\">TIT 3:3–3:7</a></p>\n<h2>The renewed mind of the believer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Renewal brings knowledge of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:9-Col1:10\">COL 1:9–1:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Renewal brings peace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:7\">PHP 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:3\">ISA 26:3</a></p>\n<h3>Renewal leads to obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5\">ROM 8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:25\">ROM 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1-Col3:2\">COL 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:13\">1PE 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:10\">HEB 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:16\">HEB 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a></p>\n<h3>The believer's mind needs growth and renewal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3\">2CO 11:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:22-Rom7:23\">ROM 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17\">EPH 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:9\">COL 1:9</a></p>",
